# 🔧 SAVY Platform Chrome

Shared rules that apply across **every** page/tool in the app.

## 🎨 Brand Constants

| Token | Value | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `--crimson` | `#DC143C` | Brand accent, logo highlight, active nav |
| App chrome | `#0A0A0A` | Header bar, body background behind pages |
| Theme color | `#0A0A0A` | PWA chrome, meta tag |

## 🔤 Fonts (loaded in layout.tsx)

| Role | Font | Fallback |
|------|------|----------|
| Display / editorial | `Playfair Display` | Georgia, serif |
| UI / labels / buttons | `Inter` | -apple-system, sans-serif |

**Rules:**
- Never add new font imports without explicit approval
- Playfair = headlines, titles, editorial moments
- Inter = everything else (buttons, labels, body, metadata)

## 📐 Layout

- `content-width` class = max 720px centered, expands on desktop
- Mobile-first: all tools target 480px max inner width
- Safe area insets: always use `env(safe-area-inset-*)` for fixed elements

## 🧭 Navigation (SavySiteHeader + SavyMobileMenu)

- Black `#0A0A0A` header bar with circular logo (40px)
- Hamburger → full-screen black overlay menu
- Nav items: uppercase Inter 600, `0.12rem` letter-spacing
- Active route = crimson text + crimson dot
- Menu animation: `savyMenuFadeIn` 0.2s ease-out

## 🚫 Don'ts

- Don't change header background from `#0A0A0A`
- Don't add nav items to `SavyMobileMenu` without updating `NAV_ITEMS` array
- Don't use colors from one page's palette on another page (each tool owns its own palette)
- Don't hardcode hex values — use CSS variables from `globals.css` when they exist
